Starting with meetings dating back to early 2016, Cash Paymaster Services&#8217; responding affidavit, filed in the Constitutional Court, provides a record of the invitations, deadlines and requests the company made to Sassa to engage on the transition arrangements. These were all to no avail until the parties finally met for the first time on 1 March, exactly one month before the ConCourt deadline.Read the affidavit for yourself here, which includes copies of the correspondence by Net1 founder Serge Belamant to Sassa executives and social development minister Bathabile Dlamini herself in Annexure A.